Türkçe
Digitoy Games
Gizlilik Politikası
Son Güncellenme Tarihi: 20 Kasım 2024
Digitoy İnteraktif Teknolojileri Bilişim Yazılım Ticaret Limited Şirketi (“
Digitoy
”) kişisel verilerinizin korunmasına önem vermektedir. Digitoy ve bağlı şirketleri, vekilleri, danışmanları, çalışanları, yöneticileri ve müdürleri topluca “
Digitoy Games
” ve “
biz
” olarak anılacaktır. İşbu gizlilik politikası ve ilgili Kişisel Verilerin Korunması Aydınlatma Metinleri (hepsi birlikte “Gizlilik Politikası” olarak anılacaktır) aracılığıyla kişisel verilerinizi işlediğimiz faaliyetler hakkında sizlere bilgi sağlamaktayız.
Digitoy Games çeşitli çevrimiçi ve mobil oyunlar sunmaktadır. Gizlilik Politikamız,
https://www.digitoygames.com
adresinde ve/veya Digitoy Games tarafından işletilen diğer alan adlarında, mobil uygulamalarda veya web sitelerinde (“
Platformlar
”) sunduğumuz oyunlarımız, ürünlerimiz, hizmetlerimiz veya içeriklerimiz gibi hizmetlerimizi (“
Hizmetler
”) kullandığınız her zaman geçerlidir. Bu Gizlilik Politikası, verilerinizi işleme yöntemlerimizi ve AB Genel Veri Koruma Tüzüğü (“
GDPR
”), 6698 sayılı Kişisel Verilerin Korunması Kanunu (“
KVKK
”) ve ilgili mevzuat uyarınca bu kişisel verilerinizle ilgili haklarınızı ve tercihlerinizi açıklar. Lütfen Digitoy Games'in üçüncü tarafların eylemlerinden, sitelerinin içeriğinden, kendilerine sağladığınız bilgilerin kullanımından veya sunabilecekleri herhangi bir hizmetten sorumlu olmadığını unutmayın.
Digitoy Games'in mevcut olduğu belirli ülkeler ve/veya bölgeler için veri koruma uygulamaları ve aydınlatma metinleri (“
Kişisel Verilerin Korunması Aydınlatma Metinleri
”) aşağıdaki gibidir:
Avrupa Birliği için lütfen aşağıdaki
“
Digitoy Games GDPR Privacy Notice for the Users
”
metnini kontrol edin.
Türkiye için lütfen aşağıdaki
“
Digitoy Games Kişisel Verilerinin Korunmasına İlişkin Kullanıcı Aydınlatma Metni
”
ni kontrol edin.
Bu Gizlilik Politikası'nı veya Kullanım Şartları'nı kabul etmiyorsanız lütfen Hizmetleri yüklemeyin veya kullanmayın.
Digitoy Games, bu Gizlilik Politikası'nı ve/veya Kişisel Verilerin Korunması Aydınlatma Metinleri’ni değiştirme hakkını saklı tutar. Hizmetleri kullanmaya devam etmeniz, bu Gizlilik Politikası'ndaki değişiklikleri kabul ettiğiniz anlamına gelir. Gizlilik Politikamız veya uygulamalarımızla ilgili sorularınız, yorumlarınız veya endişeleriniz varsa lütfen
Bize Ulaşın.
Kişisel Verilerinizin Güvenliği
Verilerinizi korumak için azami özeni gösteriyoruz ve bu bağlamda gerekli tüm önlemleri alıyoruz.
Aldığımız önlemler kişisel verilerinizin niteliğine göre değişmektedir.
Digitoy Games hesabınızın güvenliği için, şifrenizin güçlü olmasını ve şifrenizi kimseyle paylaşmamanızı öneririz. Hizmetlerimizi kullanmayı bitirdiğinizde Digitoy Games hesabınızdan ve Hizmetlerimize erişmek için kullandığınız sosyal ağ hesabınızdan çıkış yapmanızı öneririz. Digitoy Games hesabınızın güvenliğini korumanızı ve hesabınıza yetkisiz erişim olduğunu fark ederseniz derhal bize bildirmenizi rica ederiz.
Hizmetlerimizin, müşteri veri tabanımızın ve kayıtlarımızın olası güvenlik ihlallerine karşı önlemler almış olsak bile, Platformlarımızda yetkisiz erişim, bilgisayar korsanlığı faaliyetleri ve diğer veri kaybı veya veri ihlallerinin asla gerçekleşmeyeceğini garanti edemeyiz. Yapılan tüm iletimler kendi riskiniz altındadır. Web sitelerimizin güvenliğiyle ilgili herhangi bir sorunuz varsa lütfen
Bize Ulaşın.
AVRUPA BİRLİĞİ
Digitoy Games
Privacy Policy
Last Updated: 20 November 2024
Digitoy İnteraktif Teknolojileri Bilişim Yazılım Ticaret Limited Şirketi (“
Digitoy
”) attaches importance to the protection of your personal data. Digitoy and its affiliates, their proxies, consultants, employees, managers and directors shall be collectively referred to as “
Digitoy
            Games
” and “
we(s)
”. We provide you with information about the activities in which we
            process your personal data through this privacy policy and relevant Personal Data Protection
            Statements
            (all together referred to as “
Privacy Policy
”).
Digitoy Games offers a variety of online and mobile games. Our Privacy Policy applies whenever you
            use
            our services such as our games, products, services or contents (“Services”) that we provide on
https://www.digitoygames.com
, and/or
            other
            domains, mobile applications or websites operated by Digitoy Games (“
Platforms
”). This
            Privacy
            Policy describes the ways we use your data and your rights and choices concerning that personal data
            of
            yours in accordance with EU General Data Protection Regulation (“
GDPR
”), Turkish Law No. 6698
            on
            the Protection of Personal Data (“
KVKK
”) and related legislation. Please note that Digitoy
            Games
            is not responsible for the actions of third parties, the content of their sites, the use of
            information
            you provide to them or any services they may offer.
Data protection practices and statements for specific countries and/or regions where Digitoy Games is
            available (“
Personal Data Protection Statements
”) are as follows:
For European Union, please check
“
Digitoy Games GDPR
               Privacy
               Notice for the Users
”
below.
For Türkiye, please check
“
Digitoy Games Kişisel
               Verilerinin
               Korunmasına İlişkin Kullanıcı Aydınlatma Metni
”
below.
Please do not install or use the Services if you do not agree to this Privacy Policy or Terms of
            Services.
Digitoy Games reserves the right to modify this Privacy Policy and/or Personal Data Protection
            Statements. Your continued use of the Services shall mean your acceptance of the changes to this
            Privacy
            Policy. If you have questions, comments, or concerns regarding our Privacy Policy or practices,
            please
Contact Us
.
Security of Your Personal Data
We take utmost care to protect your data and take all necessary measures in this context.
The measures we take vary according to the nature of your personal data.
For the security of your Digitoy Games account, we recommend that your password is strong and that
            you do
            not share your password with anyone. We recommend that you log out of your Digitoy Games account and
            the
            social network account you use to access our Services when you are finished using them. We encourage
            you
            to maintain the security of your Digitoy Games account and notify us immediately if you discover any
            unauthorized access to your account.
Even if we have taken precautions against possible security breaches of our Services, customer
            database
            and records, we cannot guarantee that unauthorized access, hacking activities and other data loss or
            data breaches will never occur on our Platforms. All transmissions made are at your own risk. If you
            have any questions about the security of our websites, please
Contact Us
.
EUROPEAN UNION
Digitoy Games
GDPR Privacy Notice for the Users
Effective
20 November, 2024
Last Amended
20 November, 2024
This Digitoy Games GDPR Privacy Notice for the Users ("
Privacy Notice
") applies when you use our Services (
described below
) and forms an integral part of Digitoy’s
Terms of Service
. Please read it before using Digitoy Games’ Services. This document is a privacy notice and provides information about how we collect, store, use, and disclose your personal data when providing these Services to you.
I. Categories of Personal Data We Collect and How We Collect It
When you visit our Platforms or use our Services, we process your personal data in the categories below. We collect your personal data through your account and/or player profile that you have created to use our Services.
A. Data About You That You Share with Us Directly
When you use our Services, you may share your data with us directly.
Some games or parts of our Services may use a more traditional registration or account set-up process where you may be asked to share the following data with us:
your first and last name;
your username;
your gender;
your age or birthday;
your e-mail address;
a password; and/or
other data that helps us make sure it’s you accessing your account or helps us improve our services.
We may also let you create a player profile that other Digitoy Games players can see. Your player profile may include the following data:
your profile photo;
your age or age range;
the approximate physical location data that you provide;
links to your profiles on various social networks;
details about the games you play; and/or
a Digitoy Games player ID that is created by Digitoy Games and used to identify your game account (on digitoygames.com, your Digitoy Games player ID will appear in the URL of your profile page).
data about your contacts (if you share).
**Please make sure that there are no special categories of personal data (your race, ethnic origin, political opinion, philosophical belief, religion, sect or other beliefs, appearance and dress, association, foundation or trade union memberships, health, sexual life, criminal conviction and information on security measures against you) among the data you have submitted. We kindly ask you not to share any personal data that you do not prefer to be processed.**
B. Contacts Data You Share About Other Persons or Other Persons Share About You
You may invite people you know to use our Services, including by transferring your contacts to our Platforms or manually entering their contact details so that you can locate your contacts using Digitoy Games Services and invite them to join you in our games or other aspects of our Services.
We remind you that before you share this personal data with us, you must obtain the consent of the data subjects for such sharing. You are solely responsible for getting your contacts’ permission before you give their contact details to us. We may also get information about you from other Digitoy Games users importing or entering their contacts. We use and may store this contact information to help you and your contacts connect through our Services. If you want to remove your contacts stored by us, follow any instructions provided in the Service to request that we remove them from our systems or
Contact Us.
C. Data You Generate Using Our Services
When you use our Services, we’ll collect data about the ways in which you use and interact with our Services, such as when and for how long you play our games, game features and other players you interact with, purchases you make, progress or levels you achieve, and other gameplay activities.
If you choose to use communication features in Digitoy Games Services that allow you to communicate or share data with other players, then we’ll collect data on what is communicated or shared. This includes:
your participation in player forums and message boards;
your public posts or comments on other players’ profiles or gameboards;
your non-public messages or invitations to other players, made either directly on our websites or through in-game mechanisms;
your chats with other players (whether by instant message, live chat, or video); and/or your posted photos, drawings, or other user-generated content.
D. Payment Data
We’ll collect data related to any purchases you make.
If you purchase in-game virtual currency or items in a game you play on digitoygames.com, our third-party payment processor will collect the billing and financial data it needs to process your charges. This may include your personal, contact and financial data. Payment service providers do not share your financial data with Digitoy Games, including your bank or credit card details, but they may share your name, billing address and non-financial data about the items you purchased.
When you play Digitoy Games’ games or access any of our other Services on connected third-party applications or platforms (like Facebook, Apple, Google, or Amazon), any purchases you make will be processed by that third-party application and subject to that third-party application’s terms of service and privacy policy. For these purchases, Digitoy Games does not receive your financial information, but may receive non-financial information related to your purchases, like your name, approximate physical location, and the items purchased. The information Digitoy Games receives depends on the Digitoy Games’ game you’re playing and the third-party application. Please note that purchases of third-party credits or currencies are also subject to those parties’ terms of service and privacy policies.
E. Customer Support Correspondence
We’ll keep a record of any correspondence between us.
When you ask for help from our Customer Support team, we will collect and store the contact data you give them (generally, your name and e-mail address), data about your game play or activity on our Services, and your Digitoy Games player and/or social network ID number. We will also store the communications you have with our Customer Service team and any additional data in those communications in order to provide support and improve the Services.
F. Data About You That We Get from Connected Third-Party Applications, Including Social Networks
Your personal data will be collected if you access our Services through your accounts on third-party websites and applications, including social networks, or if you choose to link your accounts with these companies to our games.
Digitoy Games may collect and store some or all of the following data from the provider of the connected third-party application:
your first and last name;
your profile picture or its URL;
your user identification number (like your Facebook ID number), which may be linked to publicly-available data like your name and profile photo;
your friends’ user ID numbers and other public data;
the e-mail address you provided to that third-party application;
your approximate physical location and that of the devices you use to access our Services;
your gender;
your birthday, age, and/or age range;
data about your activities on or through the connected third-party application;
other publicly-available data on the third-party application; and/or
any other data that you or the provider of the third-party application share with Digitoy Games.
If you access our Services from a third-party application or connect our Services to a third-party
            application, you should also read that third-party application’s terms of service and privacy policy.
If you are unclear about what information a third-party application is sharing with us, please go to the
            third-party application to find out more about their privacy practices.
The data shared depends on the Digitoy Games' game that you are playing, the third-party
            application/platform you connect with our Platforms and the terms of service and privacy policy therein,
            your privacy settings, and your friends’ privacy settings, if any, on that third-party application. You
            can
            find detailed information about what data third parties’ applications/platforms share with us through
            their
            privacy policies in the links below:
Facebook:
https://www.facebook.com/privacy/center
Apple:
https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/
Google:
https://policies.google.com/privacy
Amazon:
https:www.aws.amazon.com/tr/privacy
G. Cookies and Other Automated Data Collection
We’ll collect information about your device and how you use our Services, including using cookies.
We use cookies and other similar technologies (e.g., beacons, pixel tags, clear gifs, and device identifiers) to recognize you and/or your device(s) on, off, and across different Services and devices.
            We
            also allow others to use cookies and similar technologies as described in our Cookie Notice. You can
            control
            or opt out of the use of cookies and similar technologies that track your behavior on the sites of
            others
            for third-party advertising, as described in our Cookie Notice.
We, our service providers, and our business partners use these cookies and other similar technologies to
            collect and analyze certain kinds of technical information, including:
IP address;
the type of computer or mobile device you are using;
platform type (like Apple iOS or Android);
your operating system version;
your mobile device’s identifiers, like your MAC Address, Apple Identifier For Advertising (IDFA),
               and/or
               Android Advertising ID (AAID);
application performance and de-bugging information;
your browser type and language;
referring and exit pages, and URLs;
the number of clicks on an app feature or web page;
the amount of time spent on an app feature or web page;
domain names;
landing pages;
pages viewed and the order of those pages; and/or
game state and the date and time of activity on our Services.
In some cases, we will connect the above information with your social network ID or Digitoy Games
            user
            ID.
If you play Digitoy Games’ games from a mobile device, we additionally collect the following data:
the name you have associated with your device;
your country;
your telephone number (if you provide it);
your specific geolocation (with your permission);
your mobile contacts (with your permission);
data about the Digitoy games and other third-party apps you have on your device.
H. Other Sources
To enable advertisers, ad networks and bid wall providers to serve you adverts that are more relevant to your interests, they may collect the following personal data from you using cookies and other similar tracking technologies and may use a single tracking technology or multiple tracking technologies at the same time:
performance data (such as the total number of clicks an advert receives);
certain technical data (IP address, non-permanent device identifier such as IDFA and de-identified permanent device identifier such as scrambled Android ID);
unique identifiers, such as your social network ID or Digitoy Games player ID; and/or other contextual data about your game (such as your level and session length).
II. How We Use Data We Collect and Our Legal Basis for Processing
We process your personal data for the following purposes:
to improve and optimize our Services and our players’ experiences;
to create your game accounts and allow you to play our games;
to identify and suggest connections with other Digitoy Games players and personalize our Services to you;
to communicate with you about in-game updates, and changes we make to our policies;
to enable players to communicate with each other;
to provide technical support and respond to player inquiries;
to protect the safety and well-being of our players;
to protect Digitoy’s rights and property in connection with our Services;
to prevent fraud or potentially illegal activities;
to manage and deliver contextual and behavioral advertising;
to comply with our legal obligations, resolve any disputes we may have with you or other players, and to enforce our agreements with third parties; and/or
to conduct research to improve the quality of the Services provided to you.
When we process your personal data in order to serve adverts, we rely on the following purposes:
to measure how effective the adverts are;
to deliver targeted advertising (when our Services are on and off) by displaying advertisements for products and services that are more relevant to you (this practice is known as interest-based advertising or behavioral advertising) in order to personalize your experience; and/or
to obtain web statistics, which analyze site traffic and other player activity in order to improve your experience.
We process your personal data to perform our contractual obligations; to provide you with appropriate advertising in our legitimate interests, to improve and personalize our Services; to fulfill our legal obligations and to exercise or establish our rights.
If you have any further questions about the purpose for which we collect your personal data and the legal basis for our use, or if you require any further data, please
Contact Us.
III. How We Share Data
We’ll share your data with third parties when you use our Services under the circumstances described in this section.
A. Friends and Other Digitoy Games Players
Digitoy Games’ games and Services support and often encourage you to interact with other players. In most Digitoy Games’ games, if you play through a social network or connect to a social network (for example, Facebook), your social network friends who also play a Digitoy Games’ game will see your name, photo, player profile, and a description of your activities for the game (including any Digitoy Games’ game you have played).
In addition, in many Digitoy Games’ games, other players, regardless of whether they are your social network friends, will be able to see your player profile and the identifying data in your profile (as defined above) and view descriptions of your in-game activities; communicate with you within our Services; and send you game requests or friend requests through our Services or the related social network. For example, in Okey Extra, when you are playing at a table, all the other players at the same table can see your player profile and send you an in-game chat message.
B. Third-Party Advertising Including Behavioral Advertising and Analytics
We share your personal data with advertisers based on your consent in order to tailor the advertisements you see while using our Services to your interests and to allow us to offer you some of our Services free of charge. These advertisements may include, without limitation, banner ads on game boards or Services themselves, as full-screen or in part ads, between actions or games. These third-party advertisements and advertising content are served by third-party advertisers and not by Digitoy Games, or through an “offer wall” in which third-party advertisers offer to provide virtual currency or other in-game items to players in exchange for watching an advertisement or for completing a task, such as signing up for an account with one of the advertisers, completing a survey, or finishing a particular game level. Offer walls are hosted by third-party offer wall providers, and the offers are made by third-party advertisers, not by Digitoy Games.
We do not actively share personal information that directly identifies you with third-party advertisers for their direct marketing purposes unless you give us your consent.
To enable advertisers, ad networks, and offer wall providers to serve you with more relevant ads, they may collect, or we may collect and share with them, the following types of information when you use our Services:
performance data (like the number of clicks on an advertisement);
certain technical information (like IP address, non-persistent device identifier such as IDFA, and de-identified persistent device identifier such as a hashed Android ID);
a unique identifier, such as your social network ID or Digitoy Games player ID; and/or
other contextual data about your game play (like your level and session length).
In addition to serving you with relevant ads, the information collected may be used to:
measure how effective ads are;
offer you targeted advertising (both on and off our Services) in order to personalize your experience by showing you advertisements for products and services that are more likely to appeal to you (a practice known as interest-based advertising or behavioral advertising); and/or
undertake web analytics to analyze traffic and other player activity to improve your experience.
Advertisers or ad networks may collect this information through the use of cookies and other similar tracking technologies, and they may use a single tracking technology or multiple tracking technologies at the same time.
Please note, after clicking on a third-party advertisement or offer, you may no longer be on a site or app controlled by Digitoy or the social network through which you are playing Digitoy’s games.
We would like to remind you that the actions of third parties that advertise through our Services are subject to the privacy policies of those companies.
C. Safety, Security, and Compliance with Law
We’ll share your data if necessary for safety, security, or compliance with the applicable law.
Digitoy Games may share your personal data with authorized public institutions and organizations in the following cases:
to satisfy any laws or regulations that are applicable and in force;
when we have a good faith belief that we have to disclose the data in response to lawful requests by public authorities, including for national security, law enforcement, or legal process purposes (for example, a court order, search warrant, or subpoena);
when we believe in our sole discretion that our Services are being used in committing a crime, including to report such criminal activity or to share data with other companies and organizations for the purposes of fraud protection, credit risk reduction, and other security precautions;
when we have a good faith belief that there is an emergency that poses a threat to the health and/or safety of you, another person, or the public generally;
and/or to protect the rights or property of Digitoy Games’ or applicable third parties.
Including to enforce Digitoy
Terms of Service.
D. Third-Party Service Providers
We’ll share your data with the third-party service providers and business partners that we work with to bring you, our Services.
We will share your data with third-party companies who perform services on our behalf, like payment processing, analytics, analysis, hosting services, customer service, marketing, and advertising optimization. We will also share your data with our third-party business partners who assist us in delivering and optimizing our Services, such as our platform partners
(Apple, Google, Facebook, Amazon, etc.)
. Where we share your data with third-party service providers and business partners, we ensure that we have appropriate agreements in place to protect your data
(as required by applicable data protection laws)
.
IV. Your Rights and How to Access, Update, and Manage Your Personal Data
A. European Countries Users' Rights
If you are a user located in a member state of the European Union, you have the following data
            protection
            rights in relation to your personal data in accordance with Articles 15-22 of the GDPR:
You can
access
or request
deletion
of your personal data by submitting a request via mailing to us from
info@digitoygames.com
.
You can
correct
or
update
your personal data,
object to processing
of your personal data, ask us to
restrict processing
of your personal data, or request
portability
of your personal data.
You can
opt-out of marketing communications
(if any)
.
If we have collected and processed your personal data with your consent, then you can
withdraw your consent
at any time. Withdrawing your consent will not affect the lawfulness of any processing we conducted prior to your withdrawal, nor will it affect processing of your personal data conducted in reliance on lawful processing grounds other than consent.
You have the
right to complain to a data protection authority
about our collection and use of your personal data. For more data, please contact your local data protection authority. For more, please contact your local data protection authority.
As a data subject, please contact us via
info@digitoygames.com
to exercise your above-mentioned rights. If you have any problems with Digitoy Games’ games or would like to exercise any of your other rights, you can
Contact Us
. We respond to all applications you make to us in accordance with the applicable data protection laws in accordance with the legislation.
Accessing and Deleting Personal Information Held by Digitoy Games
You can request a copy of or deletion of your game account by sending an e-mail to
info@digitoygames.com
.
To review and update personal data associated with your Digitoy Games player profile in certain games,
            visit
            the “settings” page in that game.
If you want to review or delete personal information associated with your game account data, please send
            us
            an e-mail to
info@digitoygames.com
.
In case of requests for deletion of your personal data:
We will take reasonable
            measures to
            delete your personal data from our records. We will keep certain records
(e.g., personal data relating to payments or customer service matters)
where we need
(and have rights)
to, such as for legal or accounting purposes. We’ll also keep data in order
            to
            exercise, defend, or establish our rights.
B. Managing Personal Data, We Receive from Third-Party Applications / Platforms and From Your Mobile
            Device
To manage the data, we receive from third-party applications or platforms and from your mobile device,
            please
            use the tools and settings provided by the third-party application and your mobile device.
To manage the data Digitoy Games receives about you from a third-party application or platform where you
            play our games, like Facebook, Apple, Google, or Amazon, you will need to follow the third-party
            application’s instructions for updating your data and changing your privacy settings. The privacy
            management
            tools for applications on Facebook can be found on Facebook settings section.
You also can manage many aspects of data collection and use from your mobile device by visiting the
            “settings” page of your mobile device or web browser and reviewing the access permissions of each
            Digitoy
            Games game / application.
To the extent that one of our games is collecting data about non-Digitoy Games applications you have on
            your
            mobile device, the game will provide you with an option to stop making that data available to us in the
            game’s “settings” page.
Once Digitoy Games receives your data from a third-party application / platform or your mobile device,
            that
            data is stored and used by Digitoy Games in accordance with this Privacy Notice. You may access and
            update
            that data as described above.
C. Opting Out of Third-Party Behavioral Advertising
You can opt out of third-party behavioral advertising through your device settings and other third-party
            opt-out tools.
If you are interested in more data about behavioral advertising and your choices to prevent behavioral
            web
            and mobile web advertising from third parties, you may visit the following websites:
For behavioral advertising from the US:
Network Advertising Initiative Web
                  Page
or
Digital Advertising
                  Partnership
                  Web Page
For behavioral advertising from the EU:
Online Choices Web Page
If you do not want to receive behavioral in-application advertisements from third parties that relate to your interests on your mobile device, you may adjust the ad tracking settings on your device (such as turning on “Limit Ad Tracking”). You can also reset the “Advertising Identifier” (such as an IDFA) from your mobile device’s settings page, which will prevent continued use of existing behavioral data tied to your previous “Advertising Identifier.” Further, depending on the platform provider (such as Apple or Google), you may be able to download apps, such as the Digital Advertising Alliance’s “AppChoices” app, that offer to provide you with control regarding the collection and use of cross-app data for behavioral advertising.
All of the opt-out tools described in this subsection are provided by third parties, not by Digitoy Games. Digitoy Games does not control or operate these tools or the choices that advertisers and others provide through these tools.
Please note that you may still receive third-party advertisements in Digitoy Games Services after using these opt-out tools, but the advertising you see may be less relevant to your interests.
V. Privacy Policies of Linked Third-Party Services and Advertisers
We aren’t responsible for the ways in which third parties use your data (other than our service providers acting under our instructions).
Our websites and games may contain advertisements from “Third-Party Services,” meaning companies other than Digitoy Games, that may link to their own websites, online services, or mobile applications. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of these Third-Party Services. If you have any questions about how these Third-Party Services use your data, you should review their policies and contact them directly.
Facebook:
https://www.facebook.com/privacy/center
Apple:
https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy
VI. Our Policies Concerning Children
We seek to ensure that we do not collect data from children.
Generally speaking, most of our Services are not intended for children under the age of 13 (or under 16 for children located in the European Countries) (collectively, “Children”). Children are not permitted to use these Services, and we do not knowingly collect any personal data from Children.
Though our Services do not target Children as the primary audience, we may collect age information before
            allowing a user to proceed for certain Services. For users who identify themselves as Children in our age-gate on such Services, if we allow Children to use the Services, we will either provide a version of that Service that does not collect, use, or disclose personal data, except as permitted by applicable laws, or obtain legally valid parental consent.
If we learn that we have inadvertently gathered personal information that is not subject to an exception from a Child, we will take reasonable measures to promptly remove that information from our records.
VII. International Operations and Transfers Out of European Union Countries
We may store or process your personal data outside of the country where we collect the information or the country in which you reside. We store personal data about players and visitors to our sites on Amazon Web Services (AWS) servers located in Frankfurt, Germany. Our primary place of business is in Türkiye. You should understand that we may transfer some or all of your personal data to Türkiye in order to carry out certain operational and processing needs as described in this Notice. When we transfer, store, and use personal information collected in the European Union Countries outside of the European Union Countries, we comply with our legal obligations and ensure that your personal data is subject to suitable safeguards or transferred to “approved” territories. Thus, when transferring personal data out of European Union, we implement technical, organizational, and physical safeguards to protect your personal data. We use European Commission approved standard contractual clauses and implement related measures where required by applicable law.
As part of our international operations, we may transfer personal data to our “Affiliated Entities,”
            which
            are any other corporate entities under common ownership with Digitoy or to our business partners and
            service
            providers from time to time for our legitimate business purposes. For example, Digitoy provides certain
            services to its Affiliated Entities.
The data we hold may also be processed by employees operating outside of the European Countries who work
            for
            us, one of our Affiliated Entities, or one of our business partners or service providers. This staff may
            be
            engaged in, among other things, (i) the processing of transactions and your payment details, or (ii) the
            provision of support services. When we transfer your personal data internationally, we will take
            reasonable
            steps to ensure that your personal data is treated securely, lawfully, and in the manner we describe
            here.
            Please note that laws vary from jurisdiction to jurisdiction, so the privacy laws applicable to the
            places
            where your data is transferred to or stored, used, or processed in, may be different from the privacy
            laws
            applicable to the place where you are resident.
If you have questions related to the relevant transfer mechanism for your personal data, please
Contact Us
.
VIII. How Long We Keep Your Personal Data
We destroy your personal data when the purpose of processing ceases to exist and the mandatory retention
            periods specified under the Laws and other relevant legislation expire.
While we keep your data, we take utmost care to protect your data and take all necessary measures in
            this
            context including data minimization processes. The measures we take vary according to the nature of your
            personal data. You can always reach us for deletion of your personal data.
After receiving your request to delete your account, we will destroy your data in accordance with your
            request, unless we have a valid legal reason to process your personal data.
IX. Changes to Our Privacy Notice
We’ll let you know about any material changes to this Privacy Notice.
If we decide to make material changes to our Privacy Notice, we will tell you and other players by
            placing a
            notice in-game or
https://www.digitoygames.com
or by sending you a
            notice to the e-mail address we have on file for you before the change becomes effective (and we will
            ask
            for your consent where required by law). We may supplement this process by placing notices on game
            blogs,
            social network pages, and/or player forums. You should periodically check
https://www.digitoygames.com
and this Privacy Notice for updates.
X. Contact Us
You can contact us with your questions, comments, or concerns.
If you have any questions, comments, or concerns regarding our Privacy Notice and/or privacy practices,
            please send an e-mail to info@digitoygames.com. For all other matters, please contact Digitoy through
            our
            mail,
info@digitoygames.com
or by physical mail to Digitoy
            Games,
            İYTE Teknopark A9 Binası No:14, İzmir/TÜRKİYE.
